 @coolunusual  and again, the issue here is your narrow and limited understanding of how it can be used.  Here's something I wrote in reply to someone else...

you have to use it for stuff that is important to you. Not just use it to make silly stories, create hilarious insults to use against your friends, or try to use to make political points. I've been using it a lot to help further my understanding of technical nerd stuff that I like to do. It's awesome for stuff like that because you can explain to it what you're doing and then ask questions and it will answer them in a way that has the context of what you're doing. Unlike searching google in which you might find something related, but then you have to figure how and if you can map that to your specific needs.

I also recently used it to learn how pool pump systems work because I had to figure one out. I used it in conjunction with some other resources, but I was able to use that clarify and dig into concepts that I didn't fully grasp. I would ask questions if I understood something correctly too, and it would give a reasonable response. Sure, maybe it could give some false information, but that  is why we don't just completely give in and have it guide us completely. It's a tool. A very useful tool.

